import{_ as e,o,c as t,a as s,b as r}from"./app-a6eacc5a.js";const n={},a=r('<h1 id="different-weddings" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#different-weddings" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Different Weddings</h1><p>More couples are asking <code>guests</code> to wear <code>nontraditional</code> clothing to their marriage ceremonies.</p><p>The result <em>appears to be</em> that many guests are not sure what to think about it and are confused by the unusual requests.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence</strong><br> 越来越多的新人要求宾客在结婚仪式上穿着非传统服装。</p><p>结果是，许多宾客对此感到困惑，不知道如何应对这些不寻常的要求。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> appears to be -&gt; 似乎是：用于表示某事物或情况看起来是某种状态或情况，但并不确定是否真的如此。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> guest<br><code>英 [ɡest]美 [ɡest]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 客人；特邀嘉宾，客串演员；顾客，房客；寄居昆虫<br> v. 做特邀嘉宾，客串</p></blockquote><p>nontraditional<br><code>英 [ˌnɒntrəˈdɪʃənəl]美 [nɑːntrəˈdɪʃənəl]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 不符合传统的，非传统的</p></blockquote></details><p>Maggie Long is 34 years old and lives in New York. Not too long ago, she attended the wedding of a close friend at a restaurant in Denver, Colorado. The couple described the suggested clothing for the event as, &quot;<em><code>dive</code> bar</em> <code>semiformal</code>.&quot; A dive bar is a low cost drinking place where people are not <em>known for</em> good behavior.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 玛吉·朗今年34岁，住在纽约。不久前，她在科罗拉多州丹佛市的一家餐馆参加了一位密友的婚礼。这对夫妇将婚礼的建议服装描述为“潜水酒吧半正装”。潜水酒吧是一种廉价的饮酒场所，在那里人们的行为不太好。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> dive bar -&gt; 小酒馆：一个简陋的、通常价格便宜的酒吧，常常吸引当地的常客。<br> known for -&gt; 以......而闻名：指某人或某事因为某种特点、品质或成就而广为人知。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> dive<br><code>英: [daɪv] 美: [daɪv]</code></p><blockquote><p>机，鸟）俯冲；热情投身于；快速伸入（包、口袋等）；（对方阻截时）假摔<br> n. 跳水；潜水；俯冲；突降，暴跌；冲，扑；（遇到阻截时的）假摔；低级的餐馆（或酒吧、娱乐场所）</p></blockquote><p>semiformal<br><code>英 [ˌsemɪˈfɔːməl]美 [ˌsemaɪˈfɔməl]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 半正式的</p></blockquote></details><p>&quot;I love a theme,&quot; said Long. &quot;It&#39;s fun that people aren&#39;t taking weddings so seriously, but I had no idea what that meant.&quot; At the dive bar wedding, Long said many older guests got into the idea. One guest wore a <code>rainbow</code> <code>tie-dye</code> shirt, a colorful informal shirt made popular in the 1960s.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> “我喜欢有主题的婚礼，”朗说。“婚礼不那么严肃，这很有趣，但我不知道这意味着什么。”在潜水酒吧的婚礼上，朗说许多年长的宾客都接受了这个想法。一位宾客穿着一件彩虹扎染衬衫，这是一种在20世纪60年代流行的彩色非正式衬衫。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> rainbow<br><code>英 [ˈreɪnbəʊ]美 [ˈreɪnboʊ]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 彩虹；众多花色品种，五颜六色的组合，五花八门的聚合；五彩缤纷的展示；多种颜色，五彩缤纷<br> adj. 不同种族（或文化等）人群的</p></blockquote><p>tie-dye ( tie-dyeing, tie-dyed, tie-dyes )<br><code>英 [ˈtaɪ daɪ]美 [ˈtaɪ daɪ]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 扎染（织物）<br> n. 手工扎染法；扎染布料</p></blockquote></details><p>Other wedding guests have been invited to weddings that were described as, &quot;<code>tropical</code> formal,&quot; &quot;<code>snappy</code> casual&quot; and &quot;garden party <code>whimsical</code>.&quot; Emily Coyne is <em>the <code>founder</code> of</em> Emily Coyne Events, a wedding design company based in San Francisco, California. She said many couples are trying to make their weddings different from everyone <code>else</code>&#39;s wedding.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 其他婚礼宾客受邀参加的婚礼被形容为&quot;热带正式&quot;、&quot;时髦休闲&quot;和&quot;花园派对奇思妙想&quot;。艾米莉·科因是位于加利福尼亚州旧金山的婚礼设计公司Emily Coyne Events的创始人。她说，许多新人都试图让自己的婚礼与众不同。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> the founder of -&gt; ......的创始人：指某个组织、公司或事业的创建者和发起人。</p><p><strong>words:</strong><br> tropical<br><code>英 [ˈtrɒpɪk(ə)l]美 [ˈtrɑːpɪk(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 热带的，热带地区的；（天气）湿热的</p></blockquote><p>snappy ( snappier, snappiest )<br><code>英 [ˈsnæpi]美 [ˈsnæpi]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 厉声说话的；生气勃勃的；时髦的；爽快的</p></blockquote><p>whimsical<br><code>英 [ˈwɪmzɪk(ə)l]美 [ˈwɪmzɪk(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 古怪的；异想天开的；反复无常的</p></blockquote><p>founder ( foundering, foundered, founders )<br><code>英: [ˈfaʊndə(r)] 美: [ˈfaʊndər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 创办者<br> v. 失败；破产；沉没</p></blockquote><p>else<br><code>英 [els]美 [els]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 此外，其他；否则，要不然<br> adj. 其他的，另外的</p></blockquote></details><p>&quot;The key is making sure there&#39;s communication behind the <em>dress code</em>. Don&#39;t just confuse guests,&quot; she said.</p><p>When her company designs wedding websites for couples, it includes descriptions for the dress code. The dress code is a description of the kinds of clothes <em>considered right</em> for the event. &quot;Tropical formal,&quot; for example, might include long dresses in bright colors and suits with unusual ties.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> “关键是要确保着装规范背后的沟通，不要让宾客感到困惑。”她说。</p><p>她的公司在为新人设计婚礼网站时，会对着装要求进行说明。着装要求是对适合婚礼的服装种类的描述。例如，“热带正装”可能包括色彩鲜艳的长裙和搭配不同寻常领带的西装。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> dress code -&gt; 着装要求：一种规定或建议的服装标准，通常适用于特定场合或活动，如办公室、学校或社交活动。<br> consider right -&gt; 认为正确：考虑后认为是正确的。</p></details><p>&quot;Most guests have a lot of fun with it,&quot; Coyne said.</p><p>Rikki Gotthelf attended her friend&#39;s &quot;space disco cowboy&quot; wedding. The hosts sent their guests to an <code>abandoned</code> town near Austin, Texas.</p><p>For guidance, Gotthelf <em>looked to</em> Sophie Strauss, who calls herself a &quot;<code>stylist</code> for <em>regular people</em>.&quot; Strauss suggests asking the couple <code>directly</code> if they had not made themselves clear.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 科因说:“大多数宾客都玩得很开心。”</p><p>里基·戈特尔夫参加了她朋友的“太空迪斯科牛仔”婚礼。主人把他们的宾客送到德克萨斯州奥斯汀附近的一个废弃小镇。</p><p>为了寻求指导，戈特尔夫向索菲·施特劳斯求助，她自称是“普通人的造型师”。施特劳斯建议如果不明白新人的意思，可以直接问他们。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> looked to -&gt; 寻求，期待：指望某人或某事来提供帮助、支持或解决问题。<br> regular people -&gt; 普通人：指一般的、非名人或非专业人士的人。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> abandon ( abandoning, abandoned, abandons )<br><code>英 [əˈbændən]美 [əˈbændən]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 抛弃，遗弃；（因危险）离开，舍弃；中止，不再有；放弃（信念、信仰或看法）；陷入，沉湎于（某种情感）<br> n. 放任，放纵</p></blockquote><p>stylist [ 复数 stylists ]<br><code>英 [ˈstaɪlɪst]美 [ˈstaɪlɪst]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 设计师；文体学家</p></blockquote><p>directly<br><code>英 [dəˈrektli]美 [dəˈrektli; daɪˈrektli]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 直接地，径直地；坦率地；恰好，正好；立即，很快地<br> conj. 一……就……</p></blockquote></details><p>She tells guests <em>dealing with</em> strange dress codes to remember: &quot;It&#39;s not a <code>costume</code>. Unless, of course, it&#39;s <code>literally</code> a costume party.&quot;</p><p>Often, there is some form of personal meaning behind the unusual wedding themes. Thirty-two-year-old Madison Smith is getting married in May 2024. Her dress code calls for &quot;black tie sunset <code>glam</code>.&quot;</p><p>&quot;It&#39;s in <code>honor</code> of my late grandfather,&quot; she said. &quot;His favorite thing was the sunsets where I&#39;m getting married.&quot; The wedding will be taking place on Long Beach Island, New Jersey.</p><p>She <em>hopes for</em> sunset-colored dresses that are orange, yellow, purple, blue or pink. She also wants suits with elements that are of similar, sunset colors.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 她告诉遇到奇怪着装要求的宾客，要记住:“这不是化装。当然，除非它确实是一个化装派对。”</p><p>通常，不寻常的婚礼主题背后都有某种形式的个人意义。32岁的麦迪逊·史密斯将于2024年5月结婚。她的着装要求是“晚礼服日落风情”。</p><p>“这是为了纪念我已故的祖父，”她说。“他最喜欢的是我结婚的地方的日落。”婚礼将在新泽西州的长滩岛举行。</p><p>她希望有橙色、黄色、紫色、蓝色或粉色的日落色连衣裙。她还希望看到带有类似夕阳色元素的西装。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> dealing with -&gt; 处理；对待<br> hopes for -&gt; 期待：对某事物的发生或实现抱有期望。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> costume<br><code>英 [ˈkɒstjuːm]美 [ˈkɑːstuːm]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 服装，装束；戏服，表演服装；泳衣，泳装<br> v. 给（某人）穿上特定服装<br> adj. （戏剧）古装的</p></blockquote><p>literally<br><code>英 [ˈlɪtərəli]美 [ˈlɪtərəli]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 按照字面意义地，逐字地；真正地，确实地；（用于夸张地强调）简直</p></blockquote><p>glam<br><code>英 [ɡlæm]美 [ɡlæm]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 迷人的；华丽摇滚乐的<br> n. 魅力；华丽摇滚乐<br> v. （使）自己有魅力<br> n. （Glam）（美）格莱姆（人名）</p></blockquote><p>honor ( honoring, honored, honors )<br><code>英 [ˈɒnə(r)]美 [ˈɑːnər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 荣誉；信用；头衔<br> vt. 尊敬（等于 honour）；给……以荣誉</p></blockquote></details><p>Jove Meyer is the owner of an event planning company in Brooklyn. He has dealt with dress codes that included &quot;colorful <code>cocktail</code>,&quot; and &quot;red <code>carpet</code> ready.&quot;</p><p>&quot;I always suggest couples <em>clarify exactly</em> what they mean,&quot; he said.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 乔夫·迈耶是布鲁克林一家活动策划公司的老板。他曾处理过“彩色鸡尾酒”和“红毯风”等着装要求。</p><p>他说:“我一直建议情侣们明确表达自己的意思。”</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> clarify exactly -&gt; 明确确切地澄清：表达清晰明确地澄清某件事情或观点。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> cocktail<br><code>英 [ˈkɒkteɪl]美 [ˈkɑːkteɪl]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 鸡尾酒；混合物；杂锦冷盘<br> adj. 鸡尾酒的<br> v. &lt;美&gt;喝鸡尾酒</p></blockquote><p>carpet ( carpeting, carpeted, carpets )<br><code>英 [ˈkɑːpɪt]美 [ˈkɑːrpɪt]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 地毯；覆盖地面的一层厚东西；&lt;美，非正式&gt;人工球场；地毯衣蛾<br> v. 给……铺地毯；厚厚地铺上；&lt;英，非正式&gt;训斥，斥责</p></blockquote></details><p>Brittny Drye is the <em>lead editor</em> of the wedding magazine Love Inc. She said guests should not be unwilling to ask the couple about an unusual dress code.</p><p>When couples are asking their guests to wear nontraditional clothes, &quot;they&#39;re signing themselves <em>up to be aske</em>d questions,&quot; Drye said.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 布里特妮·德瑞是婚礼杂志《爱情公司》的主编。她说，宾客不应该不愿意询问新人关于奇怪着装要求的问题。</p><p>当新婚夫妇要求宾客穿非传统服装时，“他们是在自愿接受提问。”德瑞说。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> lead editor -&gt; 主编：指一本杂志或报纸的主要编辑。<br> up to be asked -&gt; 自愿接受提问：指某人自愿接受提问或询问。</p></details>',28);function d(i,c){return o(),t("div",null,[s(" 一些新人渴望与众不同的婚礼 "),a])}const p=e(n,[["render",d],["__file","31-wedding.html.vue"]]);export{p as default};
